<sect2 id="Button(Heading 3)"><title>Button(Heading 3)</title>
<para>You could assign a <code>label</code>
<code>(Source Text)</code> and an <code>image</code>
<code>(Source Text)</code> to a button by the <code>label</code>
<code>(Source Text)</code> and <code>image</code> <code>(Source Text) </code>properties. If both are specified, the <code>dir</code> property control which is displayed up front, and the <code>orient</code> property controls whether the layout is horizontal or vertical. </para>
<para>
<graphic fileref="images/button.jpg"/> (Code Indent 2)(程式碼中的indent 請用tab鍵 )</para>
<para>&lt;button label="Left" image="/img/folder.gif" width="125px"/&gt;</para>
<para>&lt;button label="Right" image="/img/folder.gif" dir="reverse" width="125px"/&gt;</para>
<para>&lt;button label="Above" image="/img/folder.gif" orient="vertical" width="125px"/&gt;</para>
<para>&lt;button label="Below" image="/img/folder.gif" orient="vertical" dir="reverse" width="125px"/&gt;</para><sect3><title>Class Name(Heading 4)</title>
